"{\"uid\": \"inews.co.uk-sport-olympics-jack-draper-got-water-heatwave-chaos-paris-olympics-3198894\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"IMPARTIAL NEWS + INTELLIGENT DEBATE  Account  From a chaotic Olympic Village to the saunas of Roland Garros, athletes are being put last at this Games  Between them, theParis 2024organising committee and nature continue to blight these games.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 242, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 61, \"end\": 76, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"score\": 0.9999999999627107, \"rank\": 3.7280039636330654e-11, \"text\": \"Olympic Village\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\"}, {\"begin\": 94, \"end\": 107, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Open\", \"score\": 0.9999985082938322, \"rank\": 1.4917073045417695e-06, \"text\": \"Roland Garros\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Open\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Open\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"To the rain that scuppered theopening ceremonyand ruined thewater qualityin the Seine, to thecardboard beds, sub-standard food, insufficient toilet facilities and absence of air-conditioning in the Olympic Village that have upset so many athletes, we can add unseasonal heat that turned Roland Garros into a sauna.\", \"from\": 243, \"to\": 557, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 323, \"end\": 328, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.885463317269211, \"rank\": 0.12935226168836084, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 441, \"end\": 456, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"score\": 0.9999999999627107, \"rank\": 3.7280039636330654e-11, \"text\": \"Olympic Village\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\"}, {\"begin\": 530, \"end\": 543, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Open\", \"score\": 0.9999985082938322, \"rank\": 1.4917073045417695e-06, \"text\": \"Roland Garros\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Open\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Open\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After taking the first set against Taylor Fritz of the United States, British No 1 Jack Draper faded badly.\", \"from\": 559, \"to\": 666, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 594, \"end\": 606, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taylor_Fritz\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Taylor Fritz\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taylor_Fritz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taylor_Fritz\"}, {\"begin\": 614, \"end\": 627, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999827074388093, \"rank\": 1.7029238513479606e-05, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Though he was first on court, the midday start afforded little protection in conditions that would later see the mandatory heat rule triggered.\", \"from\": 667, \"to\": 810, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"When the mercury hits 30.1C, a 10-minute break between the second and third sets is enforced.\", \"from\": 811, \"to\": 904, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Draper, who has not played in comparable heat for at least four months, admitted that he must improve physically to contest matches in this heat.\", \"from\": 906, \"to\": 1051, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Nevertheless he had a point about the difficulty of rehydrating satisfactorily.\", \"from\": 1052, \"to\": 1131, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I mean, we were drinking hot water out there,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 1133, \"to\": 1189, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It was hot out there.\", \"from\": 1190, \"to\": 1212, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We were both trying our best to put up some good tennis.\", \"from\": 1213, \"to\": 1269, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Part of it is physicality, but I said to the referee that its pretty poor the players have to drink hot water in those conditions.\", \"from\": 1270, \"to\": 1400, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We did have ice towels and stuff but it's important we have good fridges to keep our water cool.\", \"from\": 1402, \"to\": 1499, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's so tough to recover when you are just not replenishing properly.\", \"from\": 1500, \"to\": 1569, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If felt like there was no escape from it [the heat] even at the change of ends.\\\"\", \"from\": 1570, \"to\": 1650, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Unable to access cold water from fridges the players were forced to use the change of ends to fill up their own bottles at a replenishing station, which ate into the two-minute recovery time between ends.\", \"from\": 1652, \"to\": 1856, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I have not played in much hotter conditions than that.\", \"from\": 1858, \"to\": 1913, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Your body really starts to fight against you.\", \"from\": 1914, \"to\": 1959, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We just have not had a lot of exposure to heat by being in the UK for a while, and being in Europe over the grass [season], we just have not experienced this level of heat and humidity.\", \"from\": 1961, \"to\": 2147, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2025, \"end\": 2027, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999970278489457, \"rank\": 2.965953998369816e-06, \"text\": \"UK\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was tough today and he did a better job of dealing with it than I did.\", \"from\": 2148, \"to\": 2221, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"You can refill, but at the change of ends I ended up not sitting down because I was refilling the drinks.\", \"from\": 2223, \"to\": 2329, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I want to sit down.\", \"from\": 2330, \"to\": 2349, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At all other tournaments you can get the water from the fridge.\", \"from\": 2350, \"to\": 2413, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At theUS Openthere is a fridge with ice, a cooler.\", \"from\": 2414, \"to\": 2464, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I do not know if it's normal, but that court [Suzanne Lenglen] does not have any shelter.\", \"from\": 2466, \"to\": 2556, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2513, \"end\": 2528, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Suzanne_Lenglen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Suzanne Lenglen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Suzanne_Lenglen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Suzanne_Lenglen\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So even when the umbrella is up the legs are in the sun\\u2026 I just thought it was pretty poor to put the players through that on court.\", \"from\": 2557, \"to\": 2689, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We should not have to fill our water up at the change of ends.\", \"from\": 2691, \"to\": 2754, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We need to sit down.\", \"from\": 2755, \"to\": 2775, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The people in the crowd were struggling just watching and sitting down, let alone playing.\", \"from\": 2776, \"to\": 2866, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And then you have to stand to fill up your water, I just do not think it's good enough.\\\"\", \"from\": 2867, \"to\": 2955, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"World No 2Coco Gauff, who lost in the third round to Donna Vekic, complained on TikTok about 10 athletes sharing just two bathrooms.\", \"from\": 2957, \"to\": 3089, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3010, \"end\": 3021, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donna_Veki\\u0107\", \"score\": 0.9999999518918241, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Donna Vekic\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donna_Veki\\u0107\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donna_Veki\\u0107\"}, {\"begin\": 3037, \"end\": 3043, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TikTok\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.25477552855485e-26, \"text\": \"TikTok\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TikTok\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TikTok\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The other nine moved out.\", \"from\": 3090, \"to\": 3115, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Australia's 400m swimming gold medallist Ariarne Titmus argued that conditions in the village were not conducive to high performance.\", \"from\": 3116, \"to\": 3249, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3116, \"end\": 3125, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9999139198519605, \"rank\": 8.595937996523288e-05, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}, {\"begin\": 3157, \"end\": 3171, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ariarne_Titmus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ariarne Titmus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ariarne_Titmus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ariarne_Titmus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Living in the village makes it hard to perform,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 3250, \"to\": 3309, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Australian team had to ship their own produce, including three tonnes of tuna and 2,400 meat pies, to compensate for a food offering in the village that was originally 60 percent vegan.\", \"from\": 3311, \"to\": 3500, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3311, \"end\": 3325, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Australian\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.584131227978561e-20, \"text\": \"The Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Australian\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Australian\"}, {\"begin\": 3315, \"end\": 3330, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_cricket_team\", \"score\": 0.9990090152823846, \"rank\": 0.0007765938653305841, \"text\": \"Australian team\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_cricket_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_cricket_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They also brought their own air conditioning units.\", \"from\": 3501, \"to\": 3552, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The rooms in the village have an eco-based water-cooling system but there is no thermostatic temperature control.\", \"from\": 3553, \"to\": 3666, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Six South Korean swimmers moved into a hotel closer to the Olympic venue to avoid long bus journeys in vehicles without air conditioning.\", \"from\": 3668, \"to\": 3805, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3678, \"end\": 3684, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korean_language\", \"score\": 0.9998469683304171, \"rank\": 0.00015072207910233994, \"text\": \"Korean\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korean_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korean_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The organisers subsequently address the issue with more additional buses but the sense remains that the Games has placed eco concerns above the performance needs of the athletes.\", \"from\": 3806, \"to\": 3984, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Impartial news + intelligent debate  All rights reserved.\", \"from\": 3986, \"to\": 4043, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00a9 2026 Associated Newspapers Limited.\", \"from\": 4044, \"to\": 4081, \"entities\": []}]}"